    contentEn: [
      "A food and beverage distributor supplying 340 retail points across the Midlands was managing inventory and delivery routing by a combination of spreadsheets, experience, and intuition. The results were predictable: 8.3% stockout rate, 14% of warehouse stock classified as slow-moving or dead stock, and delivery routes that drivers modified ad hoc based on traffic. The logistics manager knew the system was inefficient but had no clear way to improve it systematically. ML gave her the tools.",
      "**Demand Forecasting: XGBoost with 47 Features**\n\nThe first problem was forecasting: how much of each SKU to order, for each retail location, each week. The distributor stocked 1,400 SKUs across 340 locations — 476,000 SKU-location combinations, each with its own demand pattern.\n\nA multi-output XGBoost model shares information across SKUs and locations by encoding them as features alongside the core demand drivers:\n- **Time features:** week of year, day of week, days to next bank holiday, days since last delivery\n- **Location features:** store type, postcode cluster, average weekly revenue\n- **SKU features:** category (ambient/chilled/frozen), brand tier, shelf life, typical reorder frequency\n- **Demand history:** 4-week, 8-week, and 12-week rolling average, same-week-last-year, trend slope\n- **External signals:** local event flag, weather (temperature affects soft drink and ice cream demand), competitor promotions\n- **Promotional features:** current promotion flag, days since last promotion, typical promotion lift factor\n\nThe model is retrained weekly on a rolling 2-year window. MAPE on holdout: 11.2% (vs. 31.4% for previous manual forecasting). For perishable products, the 1-week forecast drives actual order quantities.",
      "**Inventory Optimisation: Safety Stock and Reorder Points**\n\nFor each SKU-location pair, the system calculates the reorder point (inventory level that triggers replenishment, covering expected demand during lead time plus safety stock buffer), safety stock (sized to the desired service level — 98.5% for high-velocity SKUs, 96% for slow movers — based on the XGBoost forecast's uncertainty intervals), and EOQ (balancing ordering cost against holding cost).\n\nThe warehouse management system receives daily replenishment recommendations. Buyers review and can override with a reason code — override data feeds back into the model as ground truth about buyer judgements the model does not capture.",
      "**Route Optimisation: OR-Tools Vehicle Routing Problem**\n\nGoogle OR-Tools solves the Vehicle Routing Problem using constraint programming and local search.\n\nDaily routing inputs: 8 delivery vehicles with different capacity constraints (refrigerated vs. ambient), 340 potential locations with delivery windows and order volumes, driver hours limits (Working Time Directive compliance), and a distance matrix calculated via Google Maps Distance Matrix API the night before.\n\nOR-Tools generates the full week's route plan every Sunday evening. Average route length improvement: down 19% in kilometres driven. More meaningful economically: driver overtime elimination and fuel savings that offset the system's operational cost in year one. The route plan is pushed to drivers via a mobile app; actual vs. planned deviations are logged and fed back into the time-per-stop estimates.",
      "**Results and Lessons for UK and Ukrainian Distribution**\n\nAfter 9 months in production:\n- Stockout rate: 8.3% to 2.2% (down 73%)\n- Slow/dead stock: 14% to 8.3% of warehouse value (down 41%)\n- Kilometres driven per week: down 19%\n- Driver overtime hours: down 88%\n- Manual buyer time on replenishment: down 65%\n- Working capital tied up in inventory: released £340K in the first 6 months\n\nFor UK FMCG and distribution businesses, the supply chain ML case is strong: margins are thin, logistics costs are high (particularly post-Brexit), and stockout penalties from major retailers are significant.\n\nFor Ukrainian distributors, the same infrastructure applies with adapted inputs: 1C/M.E.Doc for inventory data, Nova Poshta API for last-mile routing constraints. The SupplyIQ system Codeworth deployed for a Ukrainian pharmaceutical distributor (87 pharmacies, 600+ SKUs) used the same XGBoost + OR-Tools foundation with local system integrations.",
    ],
    faq: [
      { q: "Як ML покращує точність прогнозування попиту у дистрибуції?", qEn: "How does ML improve demand forecasting accuracy in distribution?", a: "XGBoost-модель з 47 ознаками (сезонність, свята, погода, акції) досягає MAPE 11.2% порівняно з 31.4% для ручного прогнозування. Модель перенавчається щотижня на 2-річному ковзному вікні.", aEn: "An XGBoost model with 47 features (seasonality, holidays, weather, promotions) achieves MAPE 11.2% compared to 31.4% for manual forecasting. The model retrains weekly on a rolling 2-year window." },
      { q: "Що таке оптимізація маршруту через OR-Tools?", qEn: "What is route optimisation using OR-Tools?", a: "Google OR-Tools вирішує задачу Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP) за допомогою constraint programming. Для 340 точок доставки та 8 вантажівок генерує оптимальний план щотижня. Результат: скорочення пробігу на 19%, усунення понаднормових водіїв.", aEn: "Google OR-Tools solves the Vehicle Routing Problem (VRP) using constraint programming. For 340 delivery points and 8 vehicles, it generates an optimal weekly plan. Result: 19% reduction in kilometres driven, elimination of driver overtime." },
      { q: "Скільки ML економить на логістиці для дистрибуторів?", qEn: "How much does ML save on logistics for distributors?", a: "За кейсом UK-дистрибутора: скорочення stockout з 8.3% до 2.2%, вивільнення £340K оборотного капіталу за 6 місяців, скорочення понаднормових водіїв на 88%. ROI за перший рік.", aEn: "Based on a UK distributor case: stockout rate reduced from 8.3% to 2.2%, £340K of working capital released in 6 months, driver overtime cut by 88%. Full ROI in year one." },
      { q: "Чи підходить ML-оптимізація ланцюга поставок для українських дистрибуторів?", qEn: "Is ML supply chain optimisation suitable for Ukrainian distributors?", a: "Так. Та сама архітектура адаптується для 1C/M.E.Doc (облік товарів) та Nova Poshta API (маршрутизація). Codeworth задеплоїв SupplyIQ для фармацевтичного дистрибутора (87 аптек, 600+ SKU).", aEn: "Yes. The same architecture adapts for 1C/M.E.Doc (inventory) and Nova Poshta API (routing). Codeworth deployed SupplyIQ for a pharmaceutical distributor with 87 pharmacies and 600+ SKUs." },
      { q: "Скільки коштує ML-система для ланцюга поставок?", qEn: "How much does an ML supply chain system cost?", a: "Базова система прогнозування попиту + автоматичне поповнення — від £12,000. Повна система з оптимізацією маршрутів та дашбордом для менеджерів — від £25,000. ROI досягається у перший рік.", aEn: "A basic demand forecasting + automated replenishment system — from £12,000. A full system with route optimisation and manager dashboard — from £25,000. ROI achieved in year one." },
    ],
