      "## UK ML Engineer Salary Ranges by City (2026)\n\nBased on aggregated data from LinkedIn, Glassdoor, Totaljobs and specialist recruiter surveys (Harnham, Xcede, Burtch Works) for H1 2026: London — Junior ML Engineer (0-2 years): £48,000-£65,000 base; Mid-level (2-5 years): £65,000-£95,000; Senior (5+ years): £90,000-£135,000; Principal/Staff: £130,000-£180,000+. Manchester — Junior: £38,000-£52,000; Mid: £52,000-£75,000; Senior: £72,000-£105,000. Edinburgh — Junior: £40,000-£55,000; Mid: £55,000-£82,000; Senior: £75,000-£110,000 (Edinburgh's financial services cluster drives premium). Bristol and Cambridge trail London by ~15-20%. Total compensation packages in London's big tech (Amazon, Google, Meta, Palantir): £120,000-£280,000 including RSUs and bonuses — 40-80% above base for senior roles.",
      "## Data Scientist vs ML Engineer vs MLOps Engineer: Role Definitions and Pay Differences\n\nThe UK market has crystallised into three distinct roles with different pay profiles. Data Scientist: primarily analytical — EDA, statistical modelling, A/B testing, business insight reporting; Python + SQL core skills; median UK salary £58,000. ML Engineer: builds and deploys production ML systems — feature pipelines, model serving, API development; Python + MLOps tools core; median UK salary £71,000 (22% premium over Data Scientist reflecting engineering scarcity). MLOps Engineer: specialises in ML infrastructure — Kubernetes, model registries (MLflow, Weights & Biases), CI/CD for models, monitoring; median UK salary £73,000. The boundaries are blurring: 'ML Engineer' increasingly covers the full spectrum from model development through deployment, with 'Applied Scientist' emerging as the title for research-oriented ML Engineers at larger UK tech firms.",
      "## Skills Premium: LLM, RAG, MLOps Adding 15-25% to Base Salary\n\nThe 2026 UK ML job market shows clear skills premiums above the base ML Engineer median: LLM fine-tuning experience (LoRA, PEFT, RLHF): +20-25% premium; RAG system design and LlamaIndex/LangChain: +15-20%; MLOps tooling depth (Kubeflow, Seldon, Bentoml, Ray): +15-20%; computer vision with production deployment: +12-18%; time-series ML for finance/energy: +10-15%. Critically, the combination of LLM + MLOps ('LLMOps') commands the highest premiums — a Senior ML Engineer who can build, fine-tune, evaluate and deploy LLMs in production is commanding £110,000-£145,000 in London, £20,000-£30,000 above the standard Senior ML Engineer range. UK GDPR and AI governance experience is emerging as a differentiator in regulated industries (fintech, insurtech, healthtech).",
