        aEn: "LLM security testing before UK launch — checklist based on OWASP LLM Top 10 (2025): (1) Prompt injection — test with 20+ adversarial prompts (classic overrides, indirect via documents, language switching). (2) Insecure output handling — can the LLM generate XSS/injection if output is inserted into HTML? (3) Training data poisoning (for fine-tuned models) — audit the dataset for malicious samples. (4) Excessive agency — can the LLM take actions (email, API calls) disproportionate to the request? (5) Over-reliance — is there human oversight for LLM-influenced decisions? (6) Sensitive disclosure — test with crafted queries to extract system prompt or training data. Document all test findings and remediation before production launch.",
