        aEn: "ML changes UK bank credit underwriting across several dimensions: (1) Better discrimination: gradient boosting (XGBoost/LightGBM) achieves 8–15 Gini points higher than traditional logistic regression scorecards due to non-linear feature interactions. (2) New data sources: Open Banking PSD2 provides 12-month transaction features — income volatility, spend patterns, subscription commitments — unavailable to bureau-only models. (3) Decision speed: automated ML decisions for straight-through cases (typically 70–80% of volume) with complex cases escalated to human underwriters. (4) IFRS 9 ECL: ML models replace manual regressions in ECL calculations, providing more accurate PD and LGD forecasts. FCA compliance: FCA PRIN 12 requires decision explainability — SHAP values are standard, fully automated AI decisions without human oversight are subject to scrutiny.",
