        aEn: "Next Best Product (NBP) ML in UK banking is typically implemented as: (1) Traditional approach — batch propensity models (logistic regression / gradient boosting) updated weekly, predicting product acceptance probability per customer. Drawback: ignores context and does not learn in real-time from rejections. (2) Contextual bandits (modern approach) — online learning algorithm (Thompson Sampling, UCB) that balances exploration/exploitation, continuously updating recommendations based on real-time accept/reject. Typical UK banking NBP funnel: current account → credit card → personal loan → mortgage / conversion. FCA COBS 4 compliance: (a) products offered must be suitable (affordability and appropriateness checks); (b) interest rate offers must show APR prominently; (c) promotional rates cannot be dark-patterned via ML. UK banks typically see 15–25% conversion rate improvement over blanket campaigns.",
