        aEn: "NCSC Cyber Assessment Framework (CAF) is the UK government framework for assessing cyber security of operators of essential services (OES) and relevant digital service providers (DSPs) under NIS regulation. CAF covers four objectives: A (managing security risk), B (protecting against cyber attack), C (detecting cyber security events), D (minimising impact of incidents). ML helps with CAF compliance via: (1) Objective B (protection): ML anomaly systems document network baselines and deviations, satisfying evidence requirements for B1 (network protection) and B3 (identity and access management). (2) Objective C (detection): ML-based threat detection satisfies C1 (security monitoring) and C2 (anomalous activity detection) — this is where ML evidence is clearest. (3) Automated evidence collection: ML platforms generate auditor-readable detection logs for CAF assessment, reducing manual audit preparation burden. UK OES sectors obligated to comply with CAF: energy, transport, water, health, digital infrastructure. Financial firms are subject to FCA PSF and PRA CP29/21 cyber resilience.",
