        aEn: "Based on UK business engagements the most valuable UK-specific time series features are: (1) Bank holidays by nation: 8 in England/Wales, 9 in Scotland, 10 in Northern Ireland — not just a binary flag but encode how many trading days remain to/from the holiday; (2) School term dates: different for each of England's 152 local authorities, larger impact than national averages for regional businesses; (3) Premier League/major sports event fixtures for F&B, transport and media; (4) Payroll cycles (UK month-end is pronounced in consumer spending); (5) Weather features (temperature, precipitation) especially for energy, food and construction. Including these UK-specific features in gradient boosted trees consistently outperforms generic models by 15–25%.",
