        aEn: "The choice between MLflow and Weights and Biases (W&B) for UK ML teams depends on several factors: (1) Cost: MLflow is entirely free when self-hosted; W&B is free for 1 user and small teams but scales to significant annual cost for large enterprises; for most UK mid-market ML teams MLflow is the pragmatic choice due to zero licence cost; (2) Data residency: self-hosted MLflow on Azure UK South guarantees UK data residency for FCA; W&B Enterprise offers region-specific hosting but requires Enterprise SLA and higher cost; (3) UI/UX: W&B has the advantage in visualisation (interactive charts, run comparison, project dashboards) — an advantage for research teams; MLflow UI is functional but simpler; (4) Regulatory pathway: MLflow's open artifact logging and vendor-independent APIs are easier to justify in FCA documentation. Recommendation: for UK FCA/NHS production ML = MLflow; for research or academic UK ML teams where UI matters more than regulatory pathway = W&B.",
