        aEn: "A/B test — ideal randomised experiment that directly measures causal effect. Causal inference — set of methods for estimating causal effects when randomised experiment is impossible (due to cost, time, or ethics). For UK business: A/B where possible, causal inference where A/B is not feasible.",
